<para>
  Isotropic thermal conductivity specifies that the <xref
  linkend="Flux-Heat_Flux"/>, <inlineequation><alt role="tex">\(\bf
  J\)</alt></inlineequation>, depends linearly and isotropically on
  the gradient of the <xref linkend="Field-Temperature"/> &field;,
  <inlineequation><alt role="tex">\(T\)</alt></inlineequation>:
  <equation>
    <alt role="tex">
      \[ {\bf J}_i = \kappa \frac{\partial T}{\partial x_i} \]
    </alt>
  </equation>
  where the conductivity <inlineequation><alt
  role="tex">\(\kappa\)</alt></inlineequation> is given by the
  parameter <varname>kappa</varname>.
</para>

